bell curves'''Bell curve''' may refer to:* A Gaussian function, a specific kind of function whose graph is a bell-shaped curve* Normal (Gaussian) distribution, whose density function is a Gaussian function* ''The Bell Curve'', a 1994 book by Richard J. Herrnstein and Charles Murray* Bell curve grading, a method of evaluating scholastic performance* The probability distribution of desirable and undesirable traits, as described in Alexander Graham Bell's essay, ""